Package co.cookies.sdk.exceptions

Provides exceptions used by the SDK that might surface to invoking developers.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CookiesRPCException
    Specifies a tree of exception types which may be encountered when processing an in-flight RPC, such as timeouts, interrupts, and background execution errors.
    CookiesSDKException
    Abstract base for all exceptions originating from the Cookies SDK for Java, including both checked exceptions (such as IOExceptions encountered when initializing) and RuntimeException descendents that surface during RPC calls.
    RPCExecutionException
    Runtime RPC processing exception thrown for all unidentified or otherwise unhandled background processing errors, including errors raised via the server (such as `INTERNAL` errors).
    RPCInterruptException
    Error class, thrown when an RPC call is interrupted while executing server-side, or interrupted while processing a callback function.
    RPCTimeoutException
    Error class, thrown when an RPC call times out while executing server-side, or generally times out for any reason whatsoever.
    ServiceSetupError
    Describes an error involving a service failing to set itself up, or initialize, or configure itself.
